{"ts": "2026-04-28T02:08:48Z", "event": "clarify_critic", "feature": "add-runtime-adoption-telemetry-via-pretooluse-bash-hook-matcher-dr-7", "findings": ["The High rating for intent clarity treats 'log invocations' and 'detect non-invocation' as one outcome — counting does not by itself implement absence detection (no inventory join, no lookback window, no zero-count semantics specified).", "The matcher predicate is undefined: sub-shells, command substitution, pipelines, xargs, fully-qualified vs PATH-resolved names, aliases, and quoted args all change the match. 'Unambiguous' is overstated when the central detection predicate is not specified.", "Scope items are scoped only by example: 'log rotation / size cap policy' has zero spec, 'weekly summary output' has no defined format/cadence/fields. Categories of work, not bounded deliverables.", "The 2026-04-27 amendment relocates the host file into the plugin tree, pulling in dual-source enforcement, just build-plugin, and plugin distribution — the 4–5-files complexity tally treats the amendment as a clarification rather than a scope expansion into the plugin build system.", "The 'no conflict with observability.md' claim ignores that observability.md enumerates exactly five subsystems and states 'No writes' as a non-functional requirement. The proposed hook writes to ~/.claude/bin-invocations.jsonl on every Bash call — a sixth subsystem the doc does not contemplate.", "'No new permission surface' was asserted, not analyzed: the hook fires on every Bash invocation including overnight (where --dangerously-skip-permissions applies) — a new automatic-execution surface triggered by sandbox-excluded commands.", "Criticality high reasoning treats this as routine 'default for shared skill changes' rather than recognizing this hook fires on a hotter path than most shared changes — every Bash call across all interactive sessions and the overnight runner; failure-mode (fail-open vs fail-closed, max latency, JSONL lock contention) is unspecified.", "The amendment pins the host file but the original 'infrastructure exists' claim relied on claude/settings.json:252-267 for hook payload shape. The amendment notes that file is 'gone post-113' but does not re-verify that the new plugin-hosted hook receives the same {tool_name, tool_input.command} payload, that ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} resolves correctly, or that adding a second entry to the existing Bash matcher does not change firing semantics for cortex-validate-commit.sh."], "dispositions": {"apply": 2, "dismiss": 6, "ask": 0}, "applied_fixes": ["Revised requirements alignment from 'ALIGNED' to 'ALIGNED with caveat': observability.md does not enumerate a runtime telemetry hook subsystem, so this introduces a new in-session-telemetry surface; the 'No writes' constraint applies to session state files (which the new JSONL is not), so no constraint conflict — but observability.md will need extension during the spec phase.", "Revised criticality reasoning to acknowledge path hotness: this hook fires on every Bash invocation across all interactive sessions AND the overnight runner; rating stays HIGH but spec must define fail-open semantics, max latency budget, and concurrency strategy for the shared JSONL log."], "dismissals": [{"finding_index": 0, "rationale": "The body explicitly names 'Wired-but-never-invoked script = DR-7-detectable failure' as the end-goal outcome. The aggregator's specific algorithm for joining inventory glob against log is spec-phase implementation detail, not Clarify-phase intent ambiguity. Intent at the Clarify level is 'what is being built and why' — both are explicit."}, {"finding_index": 1, "rationale": "Matcher command-string match semantics are research/spec concerns, not Clarify-phase intent ambiguities. Intent at Clarify rates the goal ('detect bin/cortex-* invocations'), not the implementation predicate."}, {"finding_index": 2, "rationale": "Scope boundedness in Clarify §3 evaluates whether boundaries between in-scope and out-of-scope are explicit, which they are (4 in-scope items + 2 out-of-scope items). Definitional detail for each in-scope deliverable is spec-phase work."}, {"finding_index": 3, "rationale": "The plugin distribution path is existing infrastructure — bin/cortex-* files automatically flow through just build-plugin and the dual-source pre-commit hook. The amendment uses standard distribution rather than introducing new build-system design surface. Complexity already rated complex absorbs the additional touch points."}, {"finding_index": 5, "rationale": "The PreToolUse Bash matcher pattern already fires hook scripts (cortex-validate-commit.sh) on every Bash invocation across all sessions including overnight. Adding a second entry in the existing matcher uses the same trusted execution surface — not a new permission/security surface. Defense-in-depth concern is matcher script correctness, addressed in spec."}, {"finding_index": 7, "rationale": "Infrastructure-shape verification (payload shape, ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT} resolution, firing-order with existing entries) is research-phase work. The amendment establishes host file; verifying host receives the expected JSON payload surfaces naturally as the first research question. Not a Clarify-phase blocker."}], "status": "ok"}
